#Cassandra-Installation-Instructions

Step 1. PRE-REQUISITE
Install python using https://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.7.18/python-2.7.18.amd64.msi as Cassandra CQSHL requires python

Step 2. Download cassandra
https://cassandra.apache.org/download/

Step 3. Environment Variables
   1. Add CASSANDRA_HOME=~\Cassandra\apache-cassandra-3.11.6 (Path where cassandra is installed basically the home directory)
   2. Change Path variable = Append %CASSANDRA_HOME%/bin to the end in the Path variable value
   3. Change Path variable = Append C:\Python27; to the end in the Path variable value
   4. Click Save
   
Step 4. Open Command Prompt and type cassandra and wait for a minute, you will see lines printing on the console and when it stops 
it will say that starting listening for CQL clients on localhost.

Note - Donot Close this window. Let it run!

Step 5. Open Command Prompt and type 'cqlsh'

DONE!